National Data Communications Inc said itis no longer obligated to issue its majority shareholder&lt;Signature Capital Corp> 20 mln common shares under a previousagreement.    National said it entered into a new agreement withSignature, which would have owned about 80 pct of National'scommon under the prior pact.    Under the new pact, National said it granted Signature afive-year option to acquire two mln shares of its common for anoption price equal to its current market value. National hasabout 15.3 mln shares outstanding. Reuter&#3;